Turkey Equity Movers: Alarko Carrier, Dogan Yayin, Turk Telekom

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-06-10T14:12:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-10/turkey-equity-movers-alarko-carrier-dogan-yayin-turk-telekom.html
Turkey ’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  rose 91.84, or 0.1 percent to 63,761.92 at 4:28 p.m. in
Istanbul.  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Alarko Carrier Sanayi & Ticaret AS (ALCAR TI), a maker of
heating and air conditioning equipment, surged 3.6 liras, or 10
percent, to 38.2 liras, in the biggest increase since May 10.
The company started assessments to sell an unfinished plant with
13,504 square meters (145,355 square feet) of land in Istanbul’s
Eyup district, it said in a statement to the bourse today.
 Alarko Gayrimenkul Yatirim Ortakligi AS (ALGYO)  ,  Alarko
Holding AS (ALARK) ’s real-estate unit that said it may buy
the property, rose 20 kurus, or 1.1 percent, to 18.7 liras.  Dogan Yayin Holding AS (DYHOL)  , Turkey’s biggest biggest
media group, jumped 5 kurus, or 4.6 percent, to 1.13 liras, in
the biggest increase since April 20. The company is doubling its
paid-in capital to 2 billion liras ($1.3 billion) via a rights
offering of 1 lira a share that ends today.  Turk Telekomunikasyon AS (TTKOM)  , Turkey’s biggest phone
company, advanced 16 kurus, or 2 percent, to 8.08 liras, the
highest since May 27. Morgan Stanley raised its price estimate
for Turk Telekom to 8.1 liras from 7 liras, according to an e-
mailed report today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
